"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798000","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>We have long encouraged Turkey to work towards the full protection of fundamental rights, particularly in the area of freedom of expression. The Prime Minister, the Foreign Secretary and I have all raised these issues with Turkish ministers in recent months. The Prime Minister did so most recently with her Turkish counterpart on 27 November. We will continue to engage the Turkish government on these issues and to urge respect for freedom of the media, which is essential to the long-term health of Turkish democracy.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-12-07T16:17:17.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798000/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798000/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-30","Turkey: Freedom of Expression","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his counterpart in Turkey on repression of independent media and the right to free speech in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","116907"
