"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797286","Department for Education","false","2017-12-11","<p>The proposal to remove the 50% cap on faith admissions in faith free schools is set out in the ‘<em>Schools that work for everyone’</em> consultation document (copies available in the House Library). The department plans to respond on this consultation in due course.</p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton","HL3716 ; HL3717 ; HL3719","2017-12-11T15:43:33.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797286/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797286/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-29","Church Schools: Admissions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the regional demand from parents for places in Catholic schools; and how the removal of the 50 per cent cap on faith-based admissions will meet that demand.","false","Biography information for Lord Murphy of Torfaen",,"Lord Murphy of Torfaen","HL3718"
