"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797440","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-05","<p>The Royal Navy.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-12-05T17:21:49.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797440/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797440/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-29","Armed Forces: Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 20 November 2017 to Question 112465, on armed forces: officers, from which branch of the armed forces the current Military Advisor embedded within HM Treasury Defence Spending Team came.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","116403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797441","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>NHS England does not collect information about the progress made on encouraging clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) to require providers to complete the Improving Quality in Physiological Services (IQIPS) self-assessment tool and apply for accreditation with United Kingdom Accreditation Service (UKAS) and achieve accreditation within the duration of their contract.</p><p> </p><p>However, Commissioning Services for People with Hearing Loss – a Framework for CCGs, published in July 2016, strongly encourages CCGs to expect providers to have completed the IQIPS self-assessment tool and applied for accreditation with UKAS, and achieve accreditation within the duration of their contract. This is reflected in the model service specification for adults.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-07T15:15:51.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797441/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797441/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-29","Health Services: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what progress has been made on encouraging clinical commissioning groups to require providers to complete the Improving Quality in Physiological Services (IQIPS) self-assessment tool and apply for accreditation with UKAS and achieve accreditation within the duration of their contract.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","116404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797442","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Department does not collect data and has made no estimates on the number of people who are not registered at a general practitioner practice.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-07T15:22:25.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797442/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797442/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-29","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the number of  (a) young and (b) older people who are not registered with a GP.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","116405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797443","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-07","<p>The UK has met with a wide range of countries to discuss various aspects of our trading relationship. Whilst we are still members of the EU, the UK cannot negotiate and conclude free trade agreements.</p><p>The Department for International Trade is currently engaging with all countries with which the EU has trade agreements, to discuss continuity of current trading arrangements as the UK leaves the EU. The Department has also announced a number of working groups with whom there is no EU deal in place, including the US, China, Australia, Japan and New Zealand.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-12-07T14:54:43.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797443/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797443/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-11-29","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many countries have informed his Department that they would like to have trade deals with the UK after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","116406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797444","Department of Health","false","2017-12-04","<p>No such assessment has been made. Data on individuals claiming an exemption from the prescription charge due to being in receipt of universal credit and meeting the prescribed earnings thresholds is not yet available to be collected by the NHS Business Services Authority.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-04T17:22:57.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797444/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797444/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-29","Prescriptions: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many universal credit claimants have been investigated for fraudulently claiming free prescriptions; and in how many of those investigations claimants were found to have ticked an incorrect box on the reverse of the prescription form.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","116407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797445","Home Office","false","2017-12-04","<p>The Government has no plans to introduce drug consumption rooms. A range of offences are likely to be committed in the operation of drug consumption rooms. It is for local police forces to enforce the law in such circumstances and, as with other offences of this type, we would expect them to do so.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has responded to the advice of the Advisory Council on the Misuse of Drugs on Opioid-related deaths. The Government response is available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/drug-misuse-and-dependency-government-responses-to-acmd-reports" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/drug-misuse-and-dependency-government-responses-to-acmd-reports</a>.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2017-12-04T17:23:41.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797445/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797445/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-29","Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment her Department has made of (a) evidence and (b) recommendations regarding Drug Consumptions Rooms reported by the (i) Advisory Council on the Misuse of Drugs and (ii) Volteface report, entitled Back Yard.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","116408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797446","Department of Health","false","2017-12-04","<p>The FP10 (National Health Service prescription form), GOS1 (NHS Sight Test form) and GOS3 (NHS Optical Voucher form) are being revised to include an exemption box for Universal Credit (UC). All forms will be printed in 2018 and will be circulated as soon as existing stocks are depleted. In the meantime, advice for patients in receipt of UC who meet criteria for help with health costs, should tick the box labelled Income-based Jobseeker’s Allowance on the FP10/GOS1 or GOS3 and where possible, show their UC award notice as evidence of their entitlement.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-04T17:21:46.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797446/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797446/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-29","Prescriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on what date the (a) NHS prescription form (FP10), (b) claims for NHS-funded sight tests (GOS 1) and (c) vouchers for glasses or contact lenses (GOS 3) will be amended to include a universal credit tick box.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","116409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797447","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-07","<p>I refer the Rt Hon Member to the answer I gave to the Hon Member for Garston and Halewood to Question UIN 116154 on 5 December 2017.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-07T12:16:43.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797447/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797447/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-29","Homelessness: Liverpool City Region","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether he plans to pilot the Housing First model to prevent homelessness in the Liverpool City Region.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","116410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797448","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>A breakdown of the number of education staff trained via the Autism Education Trust (AET) is not collected centrally.</p><p>The department will shortly begin discussions with the AET to consider an extension to their current contract. The final decision over an extension will be subject to agreement of a work plan and detailed deliverables.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-07T17:10:35.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797448/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797448/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-29","Autism: Special Educational Needs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 13 November to Question 112473, how many of the 150,000 education staff trained via the Autism Education Trust (AET) are (a) teachers and (b) school support staff; and what plans she has to continue the work of the trust.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","116411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797449","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-11","<p>The answer to PQ 113243 was a formal statement of the Government's policy in standard terms. That policy self-evidently includes supporting the Palestinian Authority to lay the foundations for a safe and secure Palestinian state. In line with United Nations Security Council Resolution 242 (1967) the UK has always supported the right of all parties in the region to a just and lasting peace, with secure and recognised boundaries.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-11T16:50:16.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797449/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797449/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-29","Palestinians: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 21 November 2017 to Question 113243 on Palestinians: foreign relations, for what reason his the term safe and secure is not used in respect of a future Palestinian state.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","116412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797450","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>​The British Government remains committed to supporting the establishment of a viable and sovereign Palestinian state. This means a territorially contiguous state which allows the Palestinians to realise their aspirations for self-determination and self-government. For a future Palestinian state to be viable and sovereign there must be security arrangements that ensure Palestinian freedom of movement, and demonstrate that occupation is over.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-07T14:33:58.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797450/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797450/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-29","Palestinians: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the 21 November 2017 to Question 113243 on Palestinians: foreign relations, what his Department’s definition is for  viable and sovereign.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","116413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797451","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>The incumbent British judge, Sir Christopher Greenwood, remains a Member of the Court until the end of his current term of office in February 2018. His absence will be a great loss to the Court given Sir Christopher’s outstanding record of service to the International Court of Justice (ICJ) and to the promotion of international law. His expertise and diligence are recognised by all who have worked with him or been taught by him in the UK and internationally.</p><p>Notwithstanding the absence of a British judge on the Court after the end of Sir Christopher’s term, the UK will continue to support the work of the ICJ in line with our commitment to the importance of the rule of law in the UN system and in the international community more generally.</p><p>As a founding member of the UN, a permanent member of the Security Council and the UN’s third largest donor, the UK will continue to shape and influence the global agenda for a safer, healthier, more prosperous world.</p><p> </p><p>​</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-12-07T14:27:20.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797451/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797451/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-29","International Court of Justice: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the implications are for his Department's policies of a British judge not sitting on the International Court of Justice.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","116414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797452","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-06","<p>Civil Servants and members of the Armed Forces are not permitted to bring domestic pets into Ministry of Defence (MOD) Main Building. The only exceptions to this policy are dogs which work to assist individuals who have disabilities such as visual impairment or deafness, or an animal that is on duty and performing a task that is necessary for the security of the building or its occupants such as a Police sniffer dog. The MOD is compliant with the policy.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson",,"2017-12-06T15:38:24.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797452/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797452/answer","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797452/answer/previousversion/26970","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-29","Ministry of Defence: Staff and Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether civil servants and members of the armed forces working in MoD Main Building are permitted to bring domestic pets to work.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","116415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797453","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Department for International Trade’s Defence &amp; Security Organisation and the Ministry of Defence recently held a Turkey-UK, TF-X Programme G2G Steering Committee meeting with Turkish officials to discuss how the Turkish and UK Government and industry could work closely together to progress the TF-X project.</p><p>Due to the commercially sensitive nature of these discussions, we are unable to release the agenda.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-12-07T14:39:06.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797453/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797453/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-11-29","Turkey: Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the agenda was for the discussion for the 3rd TF-X fighter aircraft programme at the steering committee meeting held in London between his Department and the Government of Turkey.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","116416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797454","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Naval Service deploys away from the United Kingdom throughout the year, to areas such as the Gulf region, the Mediterranean, and the North and South Atlantic in support of UK operations. In addition, operations are also conducted in the UK and home waters. Over the last two years, personnel from 3 Commando Brigade deployed three times on humanitarian aid and disaster relief related operations overseas.</p><p> </p><p><strong>The table below shows the number of personnel from 42 Commando, 40 Commando, and 45 Commando Royal Marines who have been deployed overseas in the last two years.</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>40 Commando</p></td><td><p>84</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>42 Commando</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>45 Commando</p></td><td><p>53</p></td><td><p>121</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Deployment refers to Military personnel who are deployed on operations for a period of 24 hours or more, excluding all personnel on overseas training excercises and those whose permanent stationed location is outside the UK.</p><p> </p><p>Notes<strong>:</strong></p><p>1. Includes only personnel who have been deployed outside of Great Britain.</p><p>2. Each individual is counted once per financial year even though they may have been deployed multiple times during that period.</p><p> </p><p><strong>The table below shows the number of occasions personnel from 42 Commando, 40 Commando, and 45 Commando Royal Marines have been deployed overseas in the last two years.</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of occasions</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong>The table below shows the number of Royal Navy and Royal Marines personnel who were deployed in the years requested.</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Navy</p></td><td><p>4,659</p></td><td><p>5,521</p></td><td><p>4,347</p></td><td><p>4,635</p></td><td><p>3,998</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Marines</p></td><td><p>1,535</p></td><td><p>1,640</p></td><td><p>1,430</p></td><td><p>869</p></td><td><p>1,040</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Notes:</p><p>1. The figures do not include Royal Navy and Royal Marine personnel conducting operations in home waters.</p><p>2. Each individual is counted once per financial year even though they may have been deployed multiple times during that period.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","116418 ; 116421 ; 116430","2017-12-07T17:52:09.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797454/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797454/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-11-29","Marines: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel from (a) 42 Commando (b) 40 Commando (c) 45 Commando Royal Marines have been deployed overseas in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","116417"
